  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And these were of the father of Etam,.... Or of the prince of Etam: or, as the Targum, these are princes that dwelt in Etam, a place not far from Zorah, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 15:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and is mentioned with Bethlehem and Tekoa in the tribe of Judah, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 11:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", namely, which follow: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Jezreel, and Ishma, and Idbash; these were the sons of the governor of Etam: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the name of their sister was Hazelelponi; who, perhaps, was a person of great note in those days, though now unknown; indeed, a Jewish chronologer (w) tells us, that the mother of Samson was Hazalelponith, of the tribe of Judah. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(w) Juchasin, fol. 10. 2.",
        "children": [
